# Cloudflare Pages redirects — Savanna
#
# Language entry point ("/"):
#   The root index.html redirects the visitor in JS to /fr/, /en/, /de/ or /it/,
#   honoring a saved choice in localStorage (falling back to /fr/, with a
#   <meta refresh> + <noscript> link as a no-JS fallback). We deliberately do
#   NOT place a hard "/  /fr/  302" rule here: Cloudflare evaluates redirects
#   before serving static assets, so an edge 302 would bypass the root page's
#   script and ignore the stored language preference. Keeping "/" client-side is
#   what makes the localStorage behavior work.
#
# www -> apex is configured as a Cloudflare redirect rule (see DEPLOYMENT.md),
# since Pages _redirects match on path only, not hostname.

# Keep build-only sources out of the served site.
/src/*          /fr/   404
/build_i18n.py  /fr/   404
